{"id":22676,"title":"Pharmacologic targets and peritoneal membrane remodeling.","abstract":"Peritoneal dialysis (PD) is associated with functional and structural changes of the peritoneal membrane, also known as peritoneal remodeling. The peritoneal membrane is affected by many endogenous and exogenous factors such as cytokines, PD fluids, and therapeutic interventions. Here, we present an overview of various studies that have investigated pharmacologic interventions aimed at regression of peritoneal damage and prolongation of PD treatment. ","date":"2014-02-14","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24525599","annotations":[{"name":"Pharmacology","weight":0.804197,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pharmacology"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Endogeny","weight":0.79024,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endogeny"},{"name":"Cell membrane","weight":0.714106,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_membrane"},{"name":"Dialysis","weight":0.705099,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dialysis"},{"name":"Peritoneal dialysis","weight":0.488317,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peritoneal_dialysis"},{"name":"Exogeny","weight":0.457728,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exogeny"},{"name":"Cytokine","weight":0.444398,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cytokine"},{"name":"Parkinson's disease","weight":0.427246,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parkinson's_disease"},{"name":"Fluid","weight":0.242405,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluid"},{"name":"Peritoneum","weight":0.104215,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peritoneum"},{"name":"Structure","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Structure"},{"name":"QT interval","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http